 </media>
<caption>"Foreigners Are Our Friends - Econ Chronicles" by the Institute for Humane Studies</caption></figure></para><para id="eip-274"><title>Watch on YouTube</title><link url="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXMnAPGY1uE" window="new">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXMnAPGY1uE</link></para></section><section id="eip-187"><title>Exercises</title><exercise id="eip-104"><problem id="eip-826">
  <para id="eip-906"><list id="write-numbers-list" mark-suffix=":" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><title>Free trade helps our economy in which of the following ways?</title><item>One country gains at the expense of another</item> 
  <item>Relatively high cost goods, services and resources are imported</item> 
  <item>Trading partners both benefit, raising the standard of living in each country</item>
  <item>Domestic production and employment shrink and prices rise.</item></list></para></problem>

<solution id="eip-905">
  <para id="eip-326">c:	Trading partners both benefit, raising the standard of living in each country. 
  </para></solution>
</exercise><exercise id="eip-716"><problem id="eip-100">
  <para id="eip-417"><list id="writenumberslist" mark-suffix=":" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><title>Who gains in a voluntary international trade?</title><item>Only the exporter</item> 
  <item>Only the importer</item> 
  <item>Both the exporter and importer</item>
  <item>Both the exporter and importer, especially the exporter</item></list> </para></problem>

<solution id="eip-239">
  <para id="eip-680">c:	Both the exporter and importer
  </para></solution>
</exercise></section></content>

